column2: start_year -  first year of model run
elapsed_year -  elapsed year of model run
dem_res -  XY resolution of DEM (meters)
dem_NoDataVal -  value representing nodata in input rasters and XYZ files
ndem -  number of DEM pixels - will be an array dimension for all DEM-level data
ndem_bi -  number of pixels in interpolated ICM-BI-DEM XYZ that overlap primary DEM
ncomp -  number of ICM-Hydro compartments - will be an array dimension for all compartment-level data
ngrid -  number of ICM-LAVegMod grid cells - will be an array dimension for all gridd-level data
neco -  number of ecoregions
nlt -  number of landtype classifications
ht_above_mwl_est -  elevation (meters) relative to annual mean water level at which point vegetation can establish
ptile_Z -  Z-value for quantile definining inundation curve
B0 -  beta-0 coefficient from quantile regression on CRMS annual inundation-salinity data (see App. A of MP2023 Wetland Vegetation Model Improvement report)
B1 -  beta-1 coefficient from quantile regression on CRMS annual inundation-salinity data (see App. A of MP2023 Wetland Vegetation Model Improvement report)
B2 -  beta-2 coefficient from quantile regression on CRMS annual inundation-salinity data (see App. A of MP2023 Wetland Vegetation Model Improvement report)
B3 -  beta-3 coefficient from quantile regression on CRMS annual inundation-salinity data (see App. A of MP2023 Wetland Vegetation Model Improvement report)
B4 -  beta-4 coefficient from quantile regression on CRMS annual inundation-salinity data (see App. A of MP2023 Wetland Vegetation Model Improvement report)
ow_bd -  bulk density of water bottoms (g/cm3)
om_k1  -  organic matter self-packing density (g/cm3) from CRMS soil data (see 2023 Wetlands Model Improvement report)
mn_k2 -  mineral soil self-packing density (g/cm3) from CRMS soil data (see 2023 Wetlands Model Improvement report)
FIBS_intvals(1)  -  FFIBS score that will serve as lower end for Fresh forested
FIBS_intvals(2)  -  FFIBS score that will serve as lower end for Fresh marsh
FIBS_intvals(3)  -  FFIBS score that will serve as lower end for Intermediate marsh
FIBS_intvals(4)  -  FFIBS score that will serve as lower end for Brackish marsh
FIBS_intvals(5)  -  FFIBS score that will serve as lower end for Saline marsh
FIBS_intvals(6)  -  FFIBS score that will serve as upper end for Saline marsh
min_accretion_limit_cm -  upper limit to allowable mineral accretion on the marsh surface during any given year [cm]
ow_accretion_limit_cm -  upper limit to allowable accretion on the water bottom during any given year [cm]
ow_erosion_limit_cm -  upper limit to allowable erosion of the water bottom during any given year [cm]
bg_lowerZ_m -  height that bareground is lowered [m]
me_lowerDepth_m -  depth to which eroded marsh edge is lowered to [m]
flt_lowerDepth_m -  depth to which dead floating marsh is lowered to [m]
mc_depth_threshold - water depth threshold (meters) defining deep water area to be excluded from marsh creation projects footprint
spsal_params[1] - SAV parameter - spring salinity parameter 1
spsal_params[2] - SAV parameter - spring salinity parameter 2
spsal_params[3] - SAV parameter - spring salinity parameter 3
sptss_params_params[1] - SAV parameter - spring TSS parameter 1
sptss_params_params_params[2] - SAV parameter - TSS salinity parameter 2
sptss_params[3] - SAV parameter - spring TSS parameter 3
dfl_params[1] - SAV parameter - distance from land parameter 1
dfl_params[2] - SAV parameter - distance from land parameter 2
dfl_params[3] - SAV parameter - distance from land parameter 3
binary_in - read input raster datas from binary files (1) or from ASCI XYZ files (0)
binary_out - write raster datas to binary format only (1) or to ASCI XYZ files (0)
dem_file -  file name with relative path to DEM XYZ file
lwf_file -  file name with relative path to land/water file that is same resolution and structure as DEM XYZ
meer_file -  file name with relative path to marsh edge erosion rate file that is same resolution and structure as DEM XYZ
pldr_file -  file name with relative path to polder file that is same resolution and structure as DEM XYZ
comp_file -  file name with relative path to ICM-Hydro compartment map file that is same resolution and structure as DEM XYZ
grid_file -  file name with relative path to ICM-LAVegMod grid map file that is same resolution and structure as DEM XYZ
dsub_file -  file name with relative path to deep subsidence rate map file that is same resolution and structure as DEM XYZ (mm/yr; positive value
ssub_file -  file name with relative path to shallow subsidence table with statistics by ecoregion (mm/yr; positive values are for downward VLM)
ssub_col - column of shallow subsidence rates to use for current scenario (1=25th percentile; 2=50th percentile; 3=75th percentile)
act_del_file -  file name with relative path to lookup table that identifies whether an ICM-Hydro compartment is assigned as an active delta site
eco_omar_file -  file name with relative path to lookup table of organic accumulation rates by marsh type/ecoregion
comp_eco_file -  file name with relative path to lookup table that assigns an ecoregion to each ICM-Hydro compartment
sav_priors_file - file name with relative path to CSV containing parameters defining the periors (per basin) for the SAV statistical model
hydro_comp_out_file -  file name with relative path to compartment_out.csv file saved by ICM-Hydro
prv_hydro_comp_out_file -  file name with relative path to compartment_out.csv file saved by ICM-Hydro for previous year
veg_out_file -  file name with relative path to *vegty.asc+ file saved by ICM-LAVegMod
monthly_mean_stage_file -  file name with relative path to compartment summary file with monthly mean water levels
monthly_max_stage_file -  file name with relative path to compartment summary file with monthly maximum water levels
monthly_ow_sed_dep_file -  file name with relative path to compartment summary file with monthly sediment deposition in open water
monthly_mi_sed_dep_file -  file name with relative path to compartment summary file with monthly sediment deposition on interior marsh
monthly_me_sed_dep_file -  file name with relative path to compartment summary file with monthly sediment deposition on marsh edge
monthly_mean_sal_file -  file name with relative path to compartment summary file with monthly mean salinity values
monthly_mean_tss_file -  file name with relative path to compartment summary file with monthly mean suspended sediment concentrations
bi_dem_xyz_file -  file name with relative path to XYZ DEM file for ICM-BI-DEM model domain - XY resolution must be snapped to XY resolution of main DEM
edge_eoy_xyz_file -  file name with relative path to XYZ raster output file for edge pixels
dem_eoy_xyz_file -  file name with relative path to XYZ raster output file for topobathy DEM
dz_eoy_xyz_file -  file name with relative path to XYZ raster output file for elevation change raster
lndtyp_eoy_xyz_file -  file name with relative path to XYZ raster output file for land type
lndchng_eoy_xyz_file -  file name with relative path to XYZ raster output file for land change flag
lndchng_eoy_xyz_file -  file name with relative path to XYZ raster output file for average salinity
lndchng_eoy_xyz_file -  file name with relative path to XYZ raster output file for maximum salinity
lndchng_eoy_xyz_file -  file name with relative path to XYZ raster output file for inundation depth
grid_summary_eoy_file -  file name with relative path to summary grid file for end-of-year landscape
grid_data_file -  file name with relative path to summary grid data file used internally by ICM
grid_depth_file_Gdw -  file name with relative path to Gadwall depth grid data file used internally by ICM and HSI
grid_depth_file_GwT -  file name with relative path to Greenwing Teal depth grid data file used internally by ICM and HSI
grid_depth_file_MtD -  file name with relative path to Mottled Duck depth grid data file used internally by ICM and HSI
grid_pct_edge_file -  file name with relative path to percent edge grid data file used internally by ICM and HSI
grid_sav_file -  file name with relative path to csv output file for SAV presence
comp_elev_file -  file name with relative path to elevation summary compartment file used internally by ICM
comp_wat_file -  file name with relative path to percent water summary compartment file used internally by ICM
comp_upl_file -  file name with relative path to percent upland summary compartment file used internally by ICM
nqaqc - number of QAQC points for reporting - as listed in qaqc_site_list_file
qaqc_site_list_file - file name with relative path to percent upland summary compartment file used internally by ICM
file naming convention prefix
